<div class="sub">
  <h1>Guides</h1>
</div>

<div class="main">
	<p>When you're just getting started or want to learn about Rails in general, the <a href="http://guides.rubyonrails.org/">Rails Guides</a> is a great way to compliment the API section as well. It's being maintained as part of <a href="http://github.com/lifo/docrails/tree/master">the docrails project</a>.</p>

</div>


<br clear="all" />

<div class="sub">
  <h1>Books</h1>
</div>

<div class="main">
	<p>
	  <a href="http://pragprog.com/titles/rails4/agile-web-development-with-rails">Agile Web Development with Rails</a> will teach you all you need to know about Ruby and Rails 3 to build killer web applications. 
	  <a href="http://pragmaticprogrammer.com/titles/fr_rr/">Rails Recipes</a> will expand on that through a wide range of tutorials of best practices.
	</p>

  <p style="text-align: center">
	  <a href="http://pragprog.com/titles/rails4/agile-web-development-with-rails" class="no_link_hover"><img src="/images/pages/documentation/awdr4.png" style="margin-left: 15px" class="bordered" width="140" height="150" /></a>

	  <a href="http://pragprog.com/book/rr2/rails-recipes/" class="no_link_hover"><img src="/images/pages/documentation/railsrecipes.gif" style="margin-left: 15px" class="bordered" width="140" height="150" /></a>
	</p>

	<p>
	  For more advanced material, Rails core member Jos√© Valim has written Crafting Rails Applications.
	</p>

  <p style="text-align: center">
	  <a href="http://pragprog.com/book/jvrails/crafting-rails-applications" class="no_link_hover"><img src="/images/pages/documentation/cra-mini.png" style="margin-left: 15px" class="bordered" width="140" height="150" /></a>
	</p>
	<p>See all the other <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/search?ie=UTF8&keywords=ruby%20on%20rails&tag=rubonrai-20&index=books&linkCode=ur2&camp=1789&creative=9325">Ruby on Rails books</a> at Amazon.</p>
</div>


<br clear="all" />

<div class="sub">
  <h1>Talking<br/>foxes?</h1>
</div>

<div class="main">
  <a href="http://media.rubyonrails.org/videos/rails_take2_with_sound.mov" class="no_link_hover"><img src="/images/pages/documentation/chunkybacon.gif" style="margin-left: 15px; margin-top: 5px" class="bordered" align="right" /></a>

	<p>
	  <a href="http://mislav.uniqpath.com/poignant-guide/">why's (poignant) guide to Ruby</a> is unlike any other guide to programming you have ever read. 
	  It features talking foxes, bizzare sidebars, and more crazy humor than most people can handle without loud chuckles. 
	</p>
</div>


